How does BMI correlate with workout type preference and session duration?¶

In [12]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = pd.read_csv(r'gym_members_exercise_tracking.csv')

# Group by Workout_Type and calculate averages
bmi_session = df.groupby('Workout_Type').agg({'BMI': 'mean', 'Session_Duration (hours)': 'mean'}).reset_index()

# Bar chart for BMI by workout type
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.bar(bmi_session['Workout_Type'], bmi_session['BMI'], color='skyblue')
plt.title('Average BMI by Workout Type')
plt.xlabel('Workout Type')
plt.ylabel('BMI')
plt.savefig("Average BMI by Workout Type.png")
plt.show()

Do individuals with higher fat percentages burn calories at a different rate during specific workout types (e.g., HIIT vs. Yoga)?¶

In [24]:
# Question 3: Fat Percentage vs. Caloric Burn by Workout Type
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns  # <-- Add this import

df = pd.read_csv(r'gym_members_exercise_tracking.csv')

# Categorize fat percentage into quartiles
df['Fat_Quartile'] = pd.qcut(df['Fat_Percentage'], q=4, labels=['Q1 (Low)', 'Q2', 'Q3', 'Q4 (High)'])

# Boxplot by workout type and fat quartile
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.boxplot(x='Workout_Type', y='Calories_Burned', hue='Fat_Quartile', data=df, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Caloric Burn by Workout Type and Fat Percentage Quartile')
plt.xlabel('Workout Type')
plt.ylabel('Calories Burned')
plt.legend(title='Fat % Quartile')
plt.savefig("Caloric Burn by Workout Type and Fat Percentage Quartile.png")
plt.show()

How do age and gender influence the choice of workout type (e.g., Strength, Cardio, HIIT, Yoga)?¶

In [27]:
# Create age groups
df['Age_Group'] = pd.cut(df['Age'], bins=[18, 30, 40, 60], labels=['18-30', '31-40', '41-60'])

# Cross-tabulate Age Group, Gender, and Workout_Type
workout_dist = pd.crosstab(index=[df['Age_Group'], df['Gender']], columns=df['Workout_Type'])

# Plot stacked bar chart
workout_dist.unstack().plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(12, 6))
plt.title('Workout Type Preference by Age Group and Gender')
plt.xlabel('Age Group & Gender')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.legend(title='Workout Type')
plt.savefig("Workout Type Preference by Age Group and Gender.png")
plt.show()

Is there a threshold for session duration (hours) beyond which average heart rate (Avg_BPM) plateaus?¶

In [44]:
# Add a polynomial trendline
import numpy as np

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.scatter(df['Session_Duration (hours)'], df['Avg_BPM'], alpha=0.5, color='orange')
z = np.polyfit(df['Session_Duration (hours)'], df['Avg_BPM'], 2)
p = np.poly1d(z)
plt.plot(np.sort(df['Session_Duration (hours)']), p(np.sort(df['Session_Duration (hours)'])), 'r--')
plt.title('Session Duration vs. Average Heart Rate')
plt.xlabel('Session Duration (hours)')
plt.ylabel('Avg BPM')
plt.savefig("Session Duration vs. Average Heart Rate.png")
plt.show()

Can workout type and frequency be clustered to identify distinct member profiles for personalized training recommendations?¶

In [64]:
# Clustering (example with k-means)
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# Preprocess data
X = df[['Workout_Frequency (days/week)', 'Session_Duration (hours)', 'Calories_Burned']]
X = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X)

# K-means clustering
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3)
df['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(X)

# PCA for visualization
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

pca = PCA(n_components=2)
X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X)

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.scatter(X_pca[:, 0], X_pca[:, 1], c=df['Cluster'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.6)
plt.title('Member Clusters (PCA Visualization)')
plt.xlabel('PCA Component 1')
plt.ylabel('PCA Component 2')
plt.savefig("Member Clusters (PCA Visualization).png")
plt.show()
